articles.title: ‘Just give us our money’: Taliban push to unlock Afghan billions abroad - The Indian Express
articles.description: Afghanistan parked billions of dollars in assets overseas with the US Federal Reserve and other central banks in Europe, but that money has been frozen since the Islamist Taliban ousted the Western-backed government in August.
articles.content: Afghanistan’s Taliban government is pressing for the release of billions of dollars of central bank reserves as the drought-stricken nation faces a cash crunch, mass starvation and a new migration cr… [+3549 chars]

articles.title: Europe’s Mars orbiter to read the signals in ‘blind’ dates with China’s rover - South China Morning Post
articles.description: Chinese probe Zhu Rong will use European orbiter to send data to Earth in communication tests – ‘blind’ because the two spacecraft use incompatible frequencies.
